The paper proposes a novel embedding model for uncertain knowledge graphs, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. The use of embedding models for knowledge graphs is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with structured knowledge, which is a topic in databases (cs.DB). The proposed model is evaluated on tasks such as relation fact ranking and classification, which are common in natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, followed by cs.DB, cs.CL, and cs.IR.
